    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required thresholds at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package for submission on the basis that the Monte Carlo UQ sweep (declared as a VerificationActivity) is understood to bound the hemolysis prediction uncertainty within clinical tolerance. All identified gaps are documented as epistemic limitations pending additional experimental data. The package is accepted as a complete submission record for regulatory review, with the expectation that outstanding factors will be addressed in a subsequent assessment cycle.",
